  "prompt": "What is the best comedy movie ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" comedy movie ever is highly subjective, as humor varies greatly from person to person. However, several comedy films are frequently cited by audiences and critics alike for their enduring appeal, originality, and impact on the genre. Here are some of the top contenders:\n\n1. **\"Some Like It Hot\" (1959)**\n   - **Director:** Billy Wilder\n   - **Stars:** Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, Jack Lemmon\n   - **Synopsis:** Two musicians disguise themselves as women to escape gangsters, leading to a series of hilarious and romantic misadventures.\n\n2. **\"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\" (1975)**\n   - **Directors:** Terry Gilliam, Terry Jones\n   - **Stars:** Graham Chapman, John Cleese, Eric Idle\n   - **Synopsis:** A surreal and irreverent take on the legend of King Arthur and his knights questing for the Holy Grail.\n\n3. **\"Airplane!\" (1980)**\n   - **Directors:** Jim Abrahams, David Zucker, Jerry Zucker\n   - **Stars:** Robert Hays, Julie Hagerty, Leslie Nielsen\n   - **Synopsis:** A spoof of disaster films where a traumatized pilot must land a plane after the crew falls ill.\n\n4. **\"Groundhog Day\" (1993)**\n   - **Director:** Harold Ramis\n   - **Stars:** Bill Murray, Andie MacDowell, Chris Elliott\n   - **Synopsis:** A cynical weatherman finds himself reliving the same day repeatedly, leading to personal growth and comedic situations.\n\n5. **\"The Big Lebowski\" (1998)**\n   - **Directors:** Joel Coen, Ethan Coen\n   - **Stars:** Jeff Bridges, John Goodman, Julianne Moore\n   - **Synopsis:** \"The Dude\" gets entangled in a complex kidnapping case after being mistaken for a wealthy namesake.\n\n6. **\"Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy\" (2004)**\n   - **Director:** Adam McKay\n   - **Stars:** Will Ferrell, Christina Applegate, Steve Carell\n   - **Synopsis:** A satirical look at a 1970s news team navigating changing times and gender dynamics.\n\n7. **\"Superbad\" (2007)**\n   - **Directors:** Greg Mottola\n   - **Stars:** Jonah Hill, Michael Cera, Christopher Mintz-Plasse\n   - **Synopsis:** High school friends embark on a mission to procure alcohol for a party, leading to comedic misadventures.\n\n8. **\"Bridesmaids\" (2011)**\n   - **Director:** Paul Feig\n   - **Stars:** Kristen Wiig, Maya Rudolph, Melissa McCarthy\n   - **Synopsis:** Competition between the maid of honor and a bridesmaid over who is the bride's best friend leads to chaotic and humorous situations.\n\n9. **\"The Grand Budapest Hotel\" (2014)**\n   - **Director:** Wes Anderson\n   - **Stars:** Ralph Fiennes, Tony Revolori, Saoirse Ronan\n   - **Synopsis:** A quirky tale of a hotel's concierge and his adventures involving a stolen painting and a family feud.\n\n10. **\"Jojo Rabbit\" (2019)**\n    - **Director:** Taika Waititi\n    - **Stars:** Taika Waititi, Scarlett Johansson, Sam Rockwell\n    - **Synopsis:** A young boy in Nazi Germany discovers his mother is hiding a Jewish girl in their home, blending satire with heartfelt moments.\n\n**Honorable Mentions:**\n- **\"Blazing Saddles\" (1974)**\n- **\"The Hangover\" (2009)**\n- **\"Hot Fuzz\" (2007)**\n- **\"Shaun of the Dead\" (2004)**\n- **\"Deadpool\" (2016)**\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" comedy movie depends on individual taste, whether one prefers slapstick, satire, dark humor, romantic comedy, or another subgenre. Exploring a variety of these films can help you find the comedy that resonates most with your sense of humor.",
